[Horse owners should be vigilant for any signs that their horse is not normal. Taking the temperature of the horse may give an early indication, as the temperature may rise a bit prior to more full blown clinical signs. Readers are referred to the moderator's comments in ProMED-mail post 20140205.2255613.

New Zealand may be located on the interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at: http://healthmap.org/r/a6Hz. - Mod.TG]
